{{pageNumber,auto}}
\page

#### Exotic Weapons
Exotic weapons are not widely available and thus few can teach how to properly use them. You do not have proficiency with exotic weapons unless your background would allow it or you find a mentor capable of teaching you.

{{note
##### Special Weapon Materials
There are no silvered or adamantine weapons available for sale on Athas. Such relics, if they ever existed, would be in the vaults of the richest merchant houses or a Sorcerer-King, or lost beneath the ruins of a civilization gone eons ago.

Metal weapons, on the other hand, do exist within Athas- they are extremely rare however, and are best represented mechanically as a +1 magic weapon or the like. 
}}

#### Improvised Weapons
Sometimes characters don’t have their weapons and have to attack with whatever is close at hand. An improvised weapon includes any object you can wield in one or two hands, such as broken glass, a table leg, a frying pan, a wagon wheel, or a dead body.

In many cases, an improvised weapon is similar to an actual weapon and can be treated as such. For example, a table leg is akin to a club. At the DM’s option, a character proficient with a weapon can use a similar object as if it were that weapon and use their proficiency bonus.

An object that bears no resemblance to a weapon deals 1d4 damage (the DM assigns a damage type appropriate to the object). If a character uses a ranged weapon to make a melee attack, or throws a melee weapon that does not have the thrown property, it also deals 1d4 damage. An improvised thrown weapon has a normal range of 20 feet and a long range of 60 feet.

## Ranged Weapon 
## Descriptions

 {{width:7px}} ***Blowgun.*** A tube of wood, bone, or hollowed horn used to fire darts by breath alone. 

***Crossbow, hand.*** A rare variant of the crossbow which fires with less force but is able to be concealed and used with one hand.

***Crossbow, heavy.*** A bow fixed to a stock, often accompanied by a stirrup which assists with the tension required to load bolts. 

***Crossbow, light.*** A lighter variant of the crossbow, firing bolts with less force but also requiring less strength to arm and carry.

***Dart.*** A small pointed missile that can be thrown. 

***Dejada.*** A long, scooped basket is worn on the arm and used to propel 2-inch ceramic or stone projectiles called “pelota” at high speed.

***Longbow.*** A tall wooden bow able to fire with great range and accuracy. 

***Shortbow.*** A smaller bow which can be drawn with greater ease but cannot fire nearly as far. 

***Sling.*** A simple weapon used to hurl stones or other small missiles. 


