}}

 {{width:7px}} ***Barding.*** A mount's defense can be reinforced by covering it with barding. Made of leather pads with bone, chitin, or wood plates, barding increases a mount's Armor Class by 2.

***Saddles.*** A pack saddle adds fifty pounds to the creature's base carrying capacity.
A riding saddle braces the rider, helping you keep your seat on an active mount in battle. It gives you advantage on any check you make to remain mounted.

***Stabling.*** Housing, feeding, and watering of animals is offered in all of the major cities. Inix and Mekillot stabling is not always available in villages, unless they are on major trade routes.


