# Drugs and Poisons

{{classTable,frame,decoration
##### Drugs of Athas

| Drug  | Type | Price  per dose |
|:---:|:-----------:|:---:|
|  Absentia  | Imbibed | 80 ct|
|Githleaf | Ingested|30 ct|
|Hypnos | Imbibed | 10 ct |
| Laq | Inhaled | 100 ct |
|Quicksilver|Injury|200 ct|
|  Voda| Injected | 120 ct |


}}

## Drug Descriptions

***Absentia.*** When you drink absentia, you fall into a comatose state and are unconscious for one hour. During this time, you perceive the world through the senses of a random creature with an Intelligence score of 5 or higher within a radius of one mile from you. The effect is similar to that of the *scrying* spell, but you perceive sensations through all five senses from the point of view of the targeted creature. The elixir cannot target anyone affected by *Hamanu's aegis*, *mind blank*, or a similar effect. Some users of absentia report that it occasionally causes bouts of sleepwalking during the comatose state induced by the substance.

Absentia's origin is unknown, but it possesses a strange hold over those who use it. Repeated use risks shaky hands and a kind of nervous disorder-- when waking from a use of absentia, you must make a DC 5 Wisdom saving throw or become cursed. While cursed, you have disadvantage on all Dexterity checks. A *remove curse* or *greater restoration* spell can remove this curse.
:

***Githleaf.*** Often sold as bundles of dried, torn plant matter called "scrap", githleaf is used by tucking a pinch between the gum and cheek. As the githleaf regains moisture, its toxins are quickly absorbed into the blood stream, causing the user to experience intense feelings of relaxation and calmness before falling into a semi-unconscious euphoria. More importantly, however, githleaf slows the user's psionic activity to such a point that they become more resilient against telepathic probes or projections, a quality that has led to a harsh Templar crackdown against the drug. 

Upon use, the user must make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become incapacitated. If they succeed, any psionics targeting them with a saving throw to resist (including spells such as *mind whip*) must reduce their DC by 2 for 1 hour. Once the effect ends, the user must make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw or become addicted. The DC increases by 2 for each use of githleaf within the past 7 days. Once addicted, the user takes 1d6 damage each day unless they use githleaf again. The withdrawals end after 5 days.

:

***Hypnos.*** This is a tasteless, odorless brew of herbs commonly peddled in Bard’s Quarters. It is typically used by bards and mindbenders to “soften up” a target before attempting to manipulate them or manifest a power. The target must make a DC 12 Constitution saving throw or suffer a 1d4 penalty modifier to saving throws against psionic effects for 1 minute.

:

***Laq.*** Laq is a vicious drug of black, syrupy venom, poured into a heated clay or porcelain pot, whose vapors are then inhaled. It induces a psychadelic effect in the user swiftly followed by voracious amounts of energy. Used excessively, it can cause a blackened tongue and a darkening of the eyes' sclera. In heavy doses it brings about raving, uncontrollable battle rage that pushes the user to fight well past the point others would die. 
 
A user of laq at normal doses must make a DC 10 Intelligence saving throw to remain focused, adding 1d4 to any Charisma or Intelligence-based skill checks for 1 hour on a success, with no benefits beyond the high on a failure. 

Any user who takes two or more doses within an hour begins to froth at the mouth as they are filled with a wild frenzy, gaining an additional action on each turn and no longer suffering the staggered condition if reduced to 0 hit points. They must immediately make a DC 20 Intelligence saving throw, suffering no additional effects on a success and losing the ability to determine friend from foe on a failure. These effects last for 1 minute, after which the user suffers one level of exhaustion and vomits profusely. 

:

***Quicksilver.*** A silvery dust of refined esperweed, created by Monks seeking greater understanding of the Way. The user must make a small incision and mix the dust with their blood until a shiny paste forms, then bind the wound like a poultice. 

Those who use this drug feel their skulls shake with psionic energies, and must roll on the table below to determine the drug's effects. 

{{classTable,frame,decoration
| d4  | Quicksilver Effects |
|:---:|:-----------:|
|  1  | Unspeakable horror causes 2d12 psychic damage|
|  2  | Lucid dreams extend your next rest by 1d10 hours |
|  3  | Gain 1 Wild Talent of your choice for 1 day |              
|  4  | Your mind buzzes. Gain 1 point of Inspiration |
}}


***Voda.*** A concentrated variant of laq which compels truth when injected. A creature subjected to voda must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become poisoned for 1 hour. The poisoned creature can't knowingly speak a lie, as if under the effect of a *zone of truth* spell.








{{pageNumber,auto}}
\page

